WEBVTT

00:01.502 --> 00:05.088
♪

00:05.088 --> 00:06.089
Oh.

00:06.089 --> 00:08.091
Aah! [ Gasps ]

00:08.091 --> 00:10.302
Still not used to that.

00:10.302 --> 00:11.678
What's the square footage
in this place?

00:11.678 --> 00:13.513
I could rent this in a day
if I were still alive

00:13.513 --> 00:15.349
and hadn't been hit
by that bus.

00:15.349 --> 00:16.683
Yeah, you've said that,
many times.

00:16.683 --> 00:18.477
You know, you don't need
to brush your teeth.

00:18.477 --> 00:19.770
There's already fluoride
in the water,

00:19.770 --> 00:20.896
and that's how
the Illuminati tracks you.

00:20.896 --> 00:22.397
Well, lucky for you,

00:22.397 --> 00:23.732
you don't have to worry
about that anymore.

00:23.732 --> 00:25.317
You don't know that.
[ Knock on door ]

00:25.317 --> 00:27.778
What?!
Is it gonna be
much longer?

00:27.778 --> 00:30.155
We agreed when you moved in,
10 minutes of bathroom time,

00:30.155 --> 00:32.157
and I got one
in the chamber.

00:32.157 --> 00:33.909
Give me a minute!
That's gross.

00:33.909 --> 00:35.202
Does he know about
this whole deal?

00:35.202 --> 00:36.537
No.
Nobody does.

00:36.537 --> 00:38.497
Are you crazy?
They'd lock her up.

00:38.497 --> 00:40.165
That's what happens
to truth tellers.

00:40.165 --> 00:41.375
I really
got to tell Dennis

00:41.375 --> 00:43.377
to stop giving me
multiple obituaries at once.

00:43.377 --> 00:45.504
Come on!
Who are you talking to, anyway?

00:45.504 --> 00:47.923
Nobody. Just listening to
a very annoying podcast.

00:47.923 --> 00:49.216
Man:
You know lying is a sin?

00:51.843 --> 00:53.220
How do you feel
about all this, Father?

00:53.220 --> 00:55.305
I'm very confused about
everything that's happening.

00:55.305 --> 00:57.182
Mm.
Maybe you should talk
to an Episcopalian.

00:59.184 --> 01:03.313
♪

01:03.313 --> 01:06.525
- Captions by VITAC--

01:06.525 --> 01:08.610
I can't believe they put <i>you</i>
in charge of this festival.

01:08.610 --> 01:10.195
I know, right?

01:10.195 --> 01:12.322
It's the newspaper's
biggest moneymaker,

01:12.322 --> 01:14.157
and usually, they give it to,
like, a section editor,

01:14.157 --> 01:16.743
and then I realized, yeah,
your girl's a section editor.

01:16.743 --> 01:18.036
Okay.
Mm-hmm.

01:18.036 --> 01:19.913
Do they know your sordid history
with the festival?

01:19.913 --> 01:21.915
Mm.
How when we were
broke staff writers,

01:21.915 --> 01:23.542
we would just steal
from all the vendors?

01:23.542 --> 01:25.210
I still can't eat
coconut shrimp.

01:25.210 --> 01:27.504
Oh, I learned real quick not to
put skewers in your pocket.

01:27.504 --> 01:28.297
I remember that.

01:30.299 --> 01:31.383
[ Laughs ]

01:31.383 --> 01:33.260
Whoa. The IT guy
got a blowout.

01:33.260 --> 01:35.846
Oh!
Sam, I'm sure you don't mind.

01:35.846 --> 01:37.598
I needed to find out
what a Karen was,

01:37.598 --> 01:39.016
and I thought it might
be a sex thing,

01:39.016 --> 01:41.059
so I didn't want to Google
from my work computer.

01:41.059 --> 01:42.936
Turns out
it's a compliment.

01:42.936 --> 01:45.814
Wow, you really got your finger
on the zeitgeist, Lexi.

01:45.814 --> 01:47.607
I know. Oh! Bad news.

01:47.607 --> 01:49.401
Bistro Eleven has had to
drop out of

01:49.401 --> 01:50.360
the food and wine festival.

01:50.360 --> 01:51.653
I know
who could replace them.

01:51.653 --> 01:53.530
Do you remember
Nyam Mat,

01:53.530 --> 01:55.657
that Swedish-Jamaican fusion
place we were obsessed with?

01:55.657 --> 01:58.618
Of course! Their jerk herring
got us through quarantine.

01:58.618 --> 02:01.330
Plus, they're really
kind of on-brand

02:01.330 --> 02:03.248
with what we were envisioning
for the event, right?

02:03.248 --> 02:06.168
Chic, sexy, but in a casual way,
just like...

02:06.168 --> 02:07.461
Tilda Swinton!
Tilda Swinton!

02:07.461 --> 02:11.757
Ha ha, yes!
I love Tilda Swinton.

02:11.757 --> 02:13.425
She's so... gaunt.

02:13.425 --> 02:14.718
Sam, you should come over
to my place tonight.

02:14.718 --> 02:16.595
Dinner on me

02:16.595 --> 02:18.764
as a little thank-you
for all of your hard work.

02:18.764 --> 02:20.724
We can finalize the layout
for the event

02:20.724 --> 02:22.517
while sipping rosé
and mocking our husbands.

02:22.517 --> 02:25.187
Yes to that.

02:25.187 --> 02:26.897
I am so sorry.
Rain check on Cricket's?

02:26.897 --> 02:28.857
Sure. No problem.

02:28.857 --> 02:31.151
I know you have
a lot on your plate. Thanks.

02:31.151 --> 02:32.986
Oh, if it helps,
I bet I can get Cricket

02:32.986 --> 02:34.404
to do a booth
for her wine bar.

02:34.404 --> 02:36.573
That would help so much.
Thank you.

02:36.573 --> 02:37.574
How sweet.

02:37.574 --> 02:38.992
Sam, why don't you come up
to my office,

02:38.992 --> 02:40.285
try out
my new massage chair?

02:40.285 --> 02:42.120
I had them take out
the restrictor plate

02:42.120 --> 02:43.622
so it really
gets in there.

02:43.622 --> 02:46.541
Mm! Great.

02:46.541 --> 02:48.460
Heh. Awesome.

02:48.460 --> 02:50.879
Yeah, have fun
in that massage chair.

02:50.879 --> 02:52.214
Me and my sciatica
will just be here

02:52.214 --> 02:55.133
uncomfortably
writing obituaries.

02:55.133 --> 02:56.301
[ Cellphone chimes ]
Oh.

02:57.844 --> 02:59.554
Dennis: Hey, hey.
Nell: Mm-hmm?

02:59.554 --> 03:01.598
Just sent you
your next obit assignment.

03:01.598 --> 03:03.850
Terri Lawrence, the puppet lady
from the '80s.

03:03.850 --> 03:05.102
Oh.
Ham Hock: Hi.

03:05.102 --> 03:07.187
I'm Ham Hock.

03:07.187 --> 03:09.690
Oh, great, a puppet lady. Awesome.

03:09.690 --> 03:11.358
Oh, I'm more
than a puppet.

03:11.358 --> 03:12.651
I'm a friend!

03:12.651 --> 03:15.529
♪

03:15.529 --> 03:19.074
Oh, Nell, I would love
to do your festival.

03:19.074 --> 03:20.784
Honey, Monty and I
used to do them all the time,

03:20.784 --> 03:22.786
and we'd have so much fun.

03:22.786 --> 03:24.538
But it's a two-person job.

03:24.538 --> 03:26.832
Maybe I can help.
You know anything about wine?

03:26.832 --> 03:27.999
I dabble.

03:27.999 --> 03:29.084
You dabble?
I do.

03:29.084 --> 03:31.128
Okay.
Tell me about that.

03:31.962 --> 03:34.172
Mm.

03:34.172 --> 03:36.508
It's very wet
on the palate.
[ Laughs ]

03:36.508 --> 03:38.885
No.
Oh.

03:38.885 --> 03:40.303
Deep garnet color.

03:40.303 --> 03:41.972
[ Sniffs deeply ]

03:41.972 --> 03:44.099
Fruit punch,
pipe tobacco.

03:44.099 --> 03:47.018
[ Slurping ]

03:47.018 --> 03:48.395
Velvety tannins.
Old World.

03:48.395 --> 03:49.646
Mm.
Southern Italy.

03:49.646 --> 03:50.981
Is this
a 2016 Primitivo?

03:50.981 --> 03:51.773
Yes!

03:51.773 --> 03:53.733
I hate it.

03:53.733 --> 03:55.026
How do you know so much
about wine?

03:55.026 --> 03:58.238
Well, when I was trying
to get my girlfriend,

03:58.238 --> 04:00.907
I read an article in <i>Glamour</i>--
"Ten Things Women Love."

04:00.907 --> 04:02.325
Wine was
at the top of the list.

04:02.325 --> 04:04.911
So, naturally, I learned
everything I could about it.

04:04.911 --> 04:07.998
Unfortunately, however,
she doesn't drink.

04:07.998 --> 04:09.124
It's too bad you're out of town
this weekend.

04:09.124 --> 04:10.917
I'm not.
She asked me not to come.

04:10.917 --> 04:11.960
Why?

04:11.960 --> 04:13.462
Women are complex. Mm.

04:13.462 --> 04:15.130
Like a 2019 Bordeaux.

04:15.130 --> 04:16.965
Oh!
Can't turn it off.

04:16.965 --> 04:18.383
So, you <i>can</i> help Cricket?

04:18.383 --> 04:20.093
Ah?
Hmm?

04:20.093 --> 04:21.178
I did get a new shirt. Oh.

04:21.178 --> 04:23.054
No tag, super soft.

04:23.054 --> 04:24.473
I'm very excited
to get into it.

04:24.473 --> 04:26.057
Okay.
Yay!

04:26.057 --> 04:27.768
You guys
are gonna love it.

04:27.768 --> 04:29.227
Oh, me and my friends always
steal from all the booths.

04:30.395 --> 04:32.731
But not yours,
of course.

04:32.731 --> 04:33.774
Huh!

04:33.774 --> 04:36.109
[ Sniffs deeply ]

04:36.109 --> 04:37.444
God, I miss bread.

04:37.444 --> 04:40.530
I am gonna eat and drink
all the food and wine

04:40.530 --> 04:43.658
at the food and wine festival
until it is just a festival.

04:43.658 --> 04:45.702
Right.
You're starving yourself.

04:45.702 --> 04:48.246
How's the
Great Sperm Detox going?

04:48.246 --> 04:51.458
Well, Ben and I are making
our deposits tonight after work.

04:51.458 --> 04:53.335
We haven't had
a single drop of alcohol

04:53.335 --> 04:55.212
or a decent bite of food
in three weeks.

04:55.212 --> 04:57.339
Oy.
Gotta keep those wigglyboys
a-squigglin'.

04:57.339 --> 04:58.340
Ew! No. Don't do that. No.

04:58.340 --> 05:00.509
Dennis: Yes. Do it.
Wonderful news, Sam.

05:00.509 --> 05:04.054
My father will now be attending
our event to see firsthand

05:04.054 --> 05:07.182
how well we're marketing
ourselves to our community.

05:07.182 --> 05:09.768
I just could not be
more... pleased.

05:09.768 --> 05:12.145
Just because he's the CEO
of a very successful

05:12.145 --> 05:14.356
media/health-supplement empire

05:14.356 --> 05:15.982
does not mean
that he's particular.

05:15.982 --> 05:17.442
No, he's very easy
to deal with,

05:17.442 --> 05:19.903
but that said, I think adding
just a couple of things

05:19.903 --> 05:22.155
that I know will get a positive
response could be the move.

05:22.155 --> 05:23.573
Lexi.
Lexi, I know your dad

05:23.573 --> 05:24.950
kind of stresses you out,
so you doing okay?

05:24.950 --> 05:26.743
Uh-huh.
Yeah, totally.

05:26.743 --> 05:28.703
[ Strained ] Uh!
You're choking me.
Needs to be tighter.

05:28.703 --> 05:31.414
Yes, listen, I think
just a couple of small things,

05:31.414 --> 05:34.668
like perhaps have a booth set up
with people hand-rolling cigars.

05:34.668 --> 05:36.503
That-- That'd be something
easy to do,

05:36.503 --> 05:38.880
and I can text you the customs
forms for his tobacco concierge.

05:38.880 --> 05:40.173
So that'll be easy.
Oh!

05:40.173 --> 05:41.883
We also need to switch out
the jazz band,

05:41.883 --> 05:43.510
because, um,
jazz agitates him.

05:43.510 --> 05:44.886
In fact, he doesn't actually
care for anything

05:44.886 --> 05:46.346
that inspires people
to move their bodies.

05:46.346 --> 05:48.139
Uh, so maybe, um,
I don't know-- bagpipes!

05:48.139 --> 05:49.558
Can you get bagpipes?

05:49.558 --> 05:50.767
Of course you can.
You're magic.

05:50.767 --> 05:52.352
[ Chuckles nervously ]

05:52.352 --> 05:54.604
Oh, I don't have
that kind of time.

05:54.604 --> 05:56.648
Ooh, speaking of time,

05:56.648 --> 05:58.733
I need you to move up
everything by two hours
to accommodate his schedule.

05:58.733 --> 06:00.110
Thank you, thank you, thank you!
You're the best.

06:00.110 --> 06:01.695
Hey.

06:01.695 --> 06:03.071
[ Chuckles ]

06:03.071 --> 06:04.823
You guys are screwed. Byeee.

06:04.823 --> 06:06.157
Is she for real?

06:06.157 --> 06:07.576
She just comes in here
and dumps work on you

06:07.576 --> 06:08.743
and messes
with your bangs,

06:08.743 --> 06:10.078
which were perfect
to begin with, by the way?

06:10.078 --> 06:11.329
No, it's fine.

06:11.329 --> 06:12.998
Her dad just throws
a lot at her.

06:12.998 --> 06:14.082
You're
a very nice person.

06:14.082 --> 06:15.625
You're like Tilda Swinton
in some movie

06:15.625 --> 06:17.002
where she does too much
for someone

06:17.002 --> 06:18.211
who doesn't appreciate her.

06:18.211 --> 06:19.754
Oh, I'm-- I'm not even sure
who she is.

06:19.754 --> 06:23.049
The point is, this doesn't
feel like a two-way street.

06:23.049 --> 06:25.635
Just because a friend
has another friend

06:25.635 --> 06:28.638
doesn't mean you can't
<i>all</i> be friends.

06:28.638 --> 06:30.181
[ Whispering ]
Quit it, pig!

06:30.181 --> 06:32.017
Look, Nell, Lexi and I
are friends, okay?

06:32.017 --> 06:33.685
So it would be really helpful
if the two of you

06:33.685 --> 06:35.854
could just figure out
a way to get along.
Of course.

06:35.854 --> 06:37.355
Just 'cause my friend
has another friend

06:37.355 --> 06:40.275
doesn't mean we can't
<i>all</i> be friends.

06:40.275 --> 06:43.278
Okay.

06:43.278 --> 06:45.530
That's what
I like to hear.

06:45.530 --> 06:47.699
But I hope
it was sincere.

06:51.161 --> 06:52.579
♪

06:52.579 --> 06:54.372
Sam: Oh, my God.

06:54.372 --> 06:56.499
This was so hard
to pull together last-minute.

06:56.499 --> 06:58.168
I can't even tell
what's real anymore.

06:58.168 --> 07:00.128
It seems like
you pulled it off.

07:00.128 --> 07:01.838
Look at this.
Dennis: Hey.

07:01.838 --> 07:04.257
Hey.
Hey.
So, we might want to
switch around the booths

07:04.257 --> 07:05.925
so people eat
before they drink,

07:05.925 --> 07:07.385
because I don't know
if it's the detox,

07:07.385 --> 07:08.845
or maybe
it's the empty stomach,

07:08.845 --> 07:11.348
but this wine
has your boy festive.

07:11.348 --> 07:12.349
Yeah, I'm so sorry.

07:12.349 --> 07:13.725
It was not supposed to be
like that.

07:13.725 --> 07:15.352
It was just changing the time
for Lexi's dad

07:15.352 --> 07:16.686
screwed everything up.

07:16.686 --> 07:19.147
Well, I desperately need
some food to soak up this wine,

07:19.147 --> 07:21.399
so Risotto Hut,
five minutes.

07:21.399 --> 07:24.944
Sam, babe, what time is
Kilta Kimbo hitting the stage?

07:24.944 --> 07:26.655
The who what now?
Kilta Kimbo.

07:26.655 --> 07:28.239
The Scottish Highland
dancing group I booked.

07:28.239 --> 07:29.491
I--
I thought your dad
hated dancing.

07:29.491 --> 07:31.493
Correct.
He does,
but he loves kicking.

07:31.493 --> 07:33.620
[ Engine revving,
horn honking ]
Ah! It's arrived.

07:33.620 --> 07:35.080
What's--
What's arrived?

07:35.080 --> 07:36.706
Why is there a monster truck
at my festival?

07:36.706 --> 07:38.249
I had it donated
so we could raffle it off.

07:38.249 --> 07:39.334
But I'm gonna make sure
Daddy wins it.

07:39.334 --> 07:40.543
[ Whispering ]
Our little secret.

07:40.543 --> 07:41.503
No, that's fraud.

07:41.503 --> 07:43.755
[ Laughing ]
You're hilarious.

07:43.755 --> 07:45.382
So, Lex, this is a little bit
more than what I was expecting

07:45.382 --> 07:47.342
when you asked me to
help you out with this festival.

07:47.342 --> 07:48.843
Oh, it's nothing my BFF
can't handle.

07:48.843 --> 07:50.720
My Best Friend,
Figuring it out.

07:50.720 --> 07:52.847
Well, no,
that would be BFFIO,

07:52.847 --> 07:54.057
and that's not even
a real thing.

07:54.057 --> 07:57.686
If I have to make room
for that truck,

07:57.686 --> 07:58.853
I'm gonna lose tables,

07:58.853 --> 08:00.438
so I might as well
just lost my mind

08:00.438 --> 08:02.482
because that seems
more efficient.
Okay, are you breathing?

08:02.482 --> 08:04.609
I don't know. My chest
is going up and down, but
nothing's going in or out.

08:04.609 --> 08:06.111
It's just
a wine festival, okay?

08:06.111 --> 08:07.153
What's the worst
that can happen?

08:07.153 --> 08:08.446
Someone could drink
without eating

08:08.446 --> 08:10.031
and they'd get dehydrated
and then they could die,

08:10.031 --> 08:11.241
then possibly
other people die,

08:11.241 --> 08:12.742
and then we'd have to go
on the lam

08:12.742 --> 08:14.202
and dye our hair blond
and move to Portugal.

08:14.202 --> 08:16.788
Portugal?
Okay, nobody's going to die.

08:16.788 --> 08:20.041
But if they did, you would look
really hot as a blonde.

08:20.041 --> 08:22.794
[ Exhales sharply ]
Okay.

08:22.794 --> 08:23.920
Okay, thank you.

08:23.920 --> 08:26.005
You got this.
Come on.

08:26.005 --> 08:27.966
Alright. Okay.

08:27.966 --> 08:30.218
I am and gonna go and make
this festival my bitch.

08:30.218 --> 08:31.177
Yes, you are. Okay.

08:31.177 --> 08:33.847
'Cause I'm your real BFF,
you know?

08:33.847 --> 08:37.183
Not like a BFF that's utterly
and truly insensitive.

08:37.183 --> 08:39.394
Yeah, 'cause that would be a
BFF-UTI, and nobody wants that.

08:39.394 --> 08:43.148
It's not nice to be mean
about someone's friend.

08:43.148 --> 08:44.566
That's right,
Ham Hock.

08:44.566 --> 08:47.360
And UTIs
are no joking matter.

08:47.360 --> 08:49.738
This isn't going
to end well.

08:49.738 --> 08:50.864
You know what
I'm in the mood for?

08:50.864 --> 08:52.323
Hmm?
Some prosciutto.

08:52.323 --> 08:54.159
[ Gasps ]

08:54.159 --> 08:55.827
And so,
much like Aladdin,

08:55.827 --> 08:59.039
we end our journey in a whole
new world with our Syrah.

08:59.039 --> 09:00.123
You can tell
they've tried to extract

09:00.123 --> 09:02.208
as much terroir
as possible.

09:04.502 --> 09:05.795
[ Laughs ] Drink.

09:06.755 --> 09:08.089
Why?

09:08.089 --> 09:10.633
Monty and I used to play
this wine-snob game.

09:10.633 --> 09:14.429
If anyone said "terroir" or
"legs" or "jammy," we'd drink.

09:14.429 --> 09:16.806
He was right about the terroir, though.

09:19.893 --> 09:22.187
I'm starting to think
that it's not the festivals

09:22.187 --> 09:24.314
that I enjoy so much.

09:24.314 --> 09:26.691
It's Monty.

09:26.691 --> 09:28.735
We could have fun anywhere.

09:28.735 --> 09:30.153
I'm sorry.

09:30.153 --> 09:32.822
I guess the heat and the sun
beating down

09:32.822 --> 09:34.240
doesn't have me
in a fun mood.

09:36.534 --> 09:39.537
[ Glasses clinking ]

09:39.537 --> 09:40.330
Excuse me.

09:41.623 --> 09:43.333
Would you mind loaning
my friend your umbrella?

09:46.628 --> 09:48.296
I don't think so.

09:48.296 --> 09:50.423
[ Whispering ] She just lost
her husband. Ohh.

09:52.008 --> 09:54.469
I'm sorry
for your loss.

09:54.469 --> 09:56.638
Yeah.
I hope this helps.

09:56.638 --> 09:57.388
Thank you.

09:57.388 --> 09:58.098
You're welcome. Aww.

09:58.098 --> 10:01.184
You know, she's also sad

10:01.184 --> 10:03.103
because she doesn't have
a lemonade.

10:03.103 --> 10:04.312
You didn't get
a lemonade?

10:04.312 --> 10:05.063
Mnh-mnh.

10:07.065 --> 10:09.150
Here you go.
Aww. Thank you.

10:09.150 --> 10:11.152
You're welcome.
Mmm!

10:11.152 --> 10:13.196
This is much tastier
than my tears.

10:14.155 --> 10:15.323
Okay.

10:15.323 --> 10:17.992
Alright now.
Bless you.
Thank you.

10:17.992 --> 10:19.661
[ Laughs ]

10:19.661 --> 10:21.955
Did we just invent
the Widow Game?

10:21.955 --> 10:24.499
I think we did.
Okay! I like it.

10:24.499 --> 10:25.625
[ Laughs ]

10:25.625 --> 10:27.377
Sam:
Okay, it's not perfect,

10:27.377 --> 10:29.212
but it could be
so much worse, right?

10:29.212 --> 10:30.588
It could be
<i>so</i> much worse.

10:30.588 --> 10:33.550
I don't know I would have done
any of this without you.

10:33.550 --> 10:34.592
Lexi: Sam?
Mm?

10:34.592 --> 10:35.927
What is this?

10:35.927 --> 10:38.096
A plate
with a hole in it.

10:38.096 --> 10:40.265
It is a hole
for your wine glass.

10:40.265 --> 10:42.142
Yeah, I took this from a woman.
She brought it from home.

10:42.142 --> 10:43.977
I'd like it back.
You stay out of this.

10:43.977 --> 10:45.270
Now, <i>this</i> is innovation.

10:45.270 --> 10:47.522
This is unique, creative.

10:47.522 --> 10:49.232
It's making all of our plates
look stupid!

10:49.232 --> 10:51.651
Okay, are you being serious
right now?

10:51.651 --> 10:54.279
Because I moved heaven and earth
to make this festival great,

10:54.279 --> 10:56.072
and now you're upset
because the plates

10:56.072 --> 10:57.740
don't have holes in them?

10:57.740 --> 11:00.201
No, I'm upset because
I hired you to do a job

11:00.201 --> 11:01.661
and you--
you dropped the ball.

11:01.661 --> 11:04.622
Oh, you hired me?
I'm someone you hire now?

11:04.622 --> 11:06.457
Because when you were stressed
and needed

11:06.457 --> 11:08.585
someone to stay up all night,
then I was your friend.

11:08.585 --> 11:10.879
Sam, make no mistake,
I am your boss,

11:10.879 --> 11:13.882
and it is your job to do
exactly what I tell you to do.

11:13.882 --> 11:15.592
And right now, it doesn't feel
like you're up for that job.

11:16.843 --> 11:18.052
Here.

11:19.012 --> 11:21.014
Whoa.

11:21.014 --> 11:22.223
I am so sorry.

11:22.223 --> 11:23.892
That was harsh
even for Lexi standards.

11:25.018 --> 11:27.187
It's fine.
No! It is not.

11:27.187 --> 11:28.688
She claims
to be your friend,

11:28.688 --> 11:29.939
and then she treats you
like crap all day.

11:29.939 --> 11:32.317
She's spoiled
and entitled,

11:32.317 --> 11:34.360
and she doesn't deserve you, dude.

11:34.360 --> 11:35.445
You know what?

11:35.445 --> 11:36.529
Actually, if she thinks

11:36.529 --> 11:38.156
that I am so terrible
at running this event,

11:38.156 --> 11:39.657
then she can run
the rest of it herself,

11:39.657 --> 11:42.911
and you and I can go off
and have fun like we used to.

11:42.911 --> 11:44.495
♪

11:44.495 --> 11:46.122
Cricket: Go!
Okay, come on.

11:46.122 --> 11:48.208
Alright.
Let's go, let's go, let's go.

11:48.208 --> 11:49.626
Yes, yes, yes.
Oh, you better hurry up.

11:49.626 --> 11:52.420
My father was, um--
he was a connoisseur himself,

11:52.420 --> 11:54.505
and--
do you have vegan--

11:54.505 --> 11:55.506
I gotta go.
Thank you.

11:55.506 --> 12:00.929
♪

12:00.929 --> 12:02.347
[ Crowd screams, gasps ]

12:04.474 --> 12:05.558
Mm!
Ah!

12:05.558 --> 12:06.851
Look at you!

12:06.851 --> 12:09.103
I don't even know
how you did that.

12:09.103 --> 12:11.356
You know what sucks?
Huh?

12:11.356 --> 12:14.651
I work my ass off
to make Lexi's event great.

12:14.651 --> 12:15.985
She doesn't appreciate
any of it.

12:15.985 --> 12:17.612
No, no, no, no, no. We don't
need to talk about Lexi.

12:17.612 --> 12:19.113
Come on.
We're having so much fun.

12:19.113 --> 12:21.032
After I pee, let's go see
if the bagpipers will let us

12:21.032 --> 12:21.908
try to play a song.

12:21.908 --> 12:23.409
You're right.

12:23.409 --> 12:24.786
And you've always been right
about her, you know?

12:24.786 --> 12:26.079
Well...
I'm done with her.

12:26.079 --> 12:28.206
She is spoiled
and entitled

12:28.206 --> 12:29.415
and she doesn't deserve me
as a friend.

12:29.415 --> 12:32.710
I tend to be
a good judge of character.

12:32.710 --> 12:34.212
Wrap it up, buddy!

12:34.212 --> 12:36.965
But the good news is,
is that I'm back.

12:36.965 --> 12:39.384
You don't need her anymore.
Heh heh!

12:39.384 --> 12:41.010
Thank you!
[ Scottish accent ]
It's all yours.

12:41.010 --> 12:43.763
To you.
Whew!

12:43.763 --> 12:45.890
Oh, yeah,
there it is.

12:45.890 --> 12:47.934
You know, someone should
actually tell Lexi

12:47.934 --> 12:50.311
to her face
that she's selfish.

12:50.311 --> 12:51.896
Uh-huh.
And that she's a butthole.

12:51.896 --> 12:53.398
Yeah, she is.
Ha!

12:53.398 --> 12:54.816
And that person
should be me right now.

12:54.816 --> 12:55.566
Huh?
Here I go.

12:55.566 --> 12:56.818
Wait, what?

12:56.818 --> 12:57.902
No, Sam,
that's a terrible idea.

12:57.902 --> 12:59.404
She's your boss.
Sam!

13:00.571 --> 13:01.656
Sam? Huh?

13:01.656 --> 13:04.242
No. Sam?
Sam?

13:04.242 --> 13:06.452
I warned you things
wouldn't end well

13:06.452 --> 13:08.371
if you didn't share
your friend.

13:08.371 --> 13:09.831
You were in there
the whole time?

13:09.831 --> 13:10.790
I saw everything.

13:11.958 --> 13:13.459
That is not cool.

13:16.087 --> 13:18.589
[ Elevator bell dings ]

13:18.589 --> 13:20.091
Uh, hey, Lexi.

13:20.091 --> 13:22.969
Um, did Sam come
to talk to you yet?

13:22.969 --> 13:24.679
No, she has not.

13:26.306 --> 13:28.391
Okay, well, it looks like
you're waiting

13:28.391 --> 13:31.352
for your dragons to hatch,
so I'll just leave you to it.

13:31.352 --> 13:34.605
This event is
a complete disaster.

13:34.605 --> 13:36.149
I stupidly made
all these changes

13:36.149 --> 13:39.569
just so my father would like it,
and now he's not even coming.

13:39.569 --> 13:42.739
His assistant texted me to say
that he can't make it,

13:42.739 --> 13:46.576
just like my graduation,
my wedding,

13:46.576 --> 13:48.536
my birth.

13:48.536 --> 13:51.247
Uh...

13:51.247 --> 13:52.623
[ Elevator bell dings ]
Alrighty.

13:52.623 --> 13:55.460
Well, it looks like you have
that under control, so bye!

13:59.338 --> 14:02.759
[ Machinery whirring ]
Ham Hock: Lexi seems sad.

14:02.759 --> 14:06.012
You should never leave
someone alone who's sad.

14:06.012 --> 14:07.430
Put a sock in it, sock.
Okay?

14:07.430 --> 14:08.931
I'm done
with the moralizing.

14:11.100 --> 14:13.895
Why do you find it so hard
to listen to good advice?

14:13.895 --> 14:15.855
Oh, my God, Terri.

14:15.855 --> 14:17.231
I'll be honest,
I completely forgot

14:17.231 --> 14:19.150
you were just a person.

14:19.150 --> 14:22.695
That's okay.
Sometimes I forget, too.

14:22.695 --> 14:26.699
Nell, when I was a child,
I had a terrible stutter.

14:26.699 --> 14:29.619
A lot of the kids
made fun of me.

14:29.619 --> 14:31.579
It made me really sad,

14:31.579 --> 14:33.748
and I closed myself off
from the rest of the world.

14:33.748 --> 14:39.253
And then one day,
I drew a face on a sock,

14:39.253 --> 14:41.547
and it made me smile,

14:41.547 --> 14:44.258
and I realized that when
I talked through the puppet,

14:44.258 --> 14:45.635
my stutter went away.

14:47.386 --> 14:49.305
Wow.
That's amazing.

14:49.305 --> 14:51.432
Ham Hock let me
talk to people,

14:51.432 --> 14:56.646
and I realized that the ones
who are the prickliest

14:56.646 --> 14:59.190
are hiding that, deep down,
they're in pain.

14:59.190 --> 15:02.568
I know that Ham Hock
may seem silly,

15:02.568 --> 15:06.405
but with her help, I make people
who are hurting feel better.

15:06.405 --> 15:10.576
And I think you can do that
for Lexi, too.

15:10.576 --> 15:14.288
♪

15:14.288 --> 15:15.665
[ Sighs ]

15:15.665 --> 15:19.001
♪

15:19.001 --> 15:20.586
Ohh.

15:20.586 --> 15:21.838
[ Elevator bell dings ]

15:21.838 --> 15:23.756
[ Exhales slowly ]

15:26.634 --> 15:27.677
You okay, bro?

15:27.677 --> 15:29.387
I'm fine.

15:29.387 --> 15:31.722
Yeah, it doesn't seem like
you're fine.

15:33.224 --> 15:34.559
Sucks that
your dad sucks, huh?

15:34.559 --> 15:35.643
What are you doing?
Why are you doing this?

15:35.643 --> 15:36.936
Who sent you?
No one.

15:36.936 --> 15:39.647
I--
Just trying to help,

15:39.647 --> 15:42.525
and it seems like
you're sad, so...

15:42.525 --> 15:44.443
Thought you might
want to talk.

15:44.443 --> 15:45.319
Fine.

15:46.946 --> 15:49.782
Yes, my father sucks.

15:49.782 --> 15:52.994
But he's always sucked.

15:52.994 --> 15:56.914
I just can't stop thinking about
how terrible I was to Sam.

15:56.914 --> 15:59.458
I mean, I said
such horrible things to her,

15:59.458 --> 16:01.752
and it's just--
it's not like me.

16:01.752 --> 16:03.296
I mean, you do that to me
all the time.

16:03.296 --> 16:04.797
Yes, because I don't care
about you.

16:04.797 --> 16:06.716
Yep.
Just like that.

16:06.716 --> 16:10.178
Look, I know that I can be
kind of... harsh

16:10.178 --> 16:12.763
and intense
and attractive,

16:12.763 --> 16:15.558
but Sam liked me anyway.

16:15.558 --> 16:18.394
She was my best friend,
and I ruined it.

16:20.188 --> 16:21.814
And I'm sure
this delights you.

16:21.814 --> 16:24.984
I mean, now you have her
all to yourself.

16:24.984 --> 16:27.486
I know that you...
dislike me.

16:30.781 --> 16:33.993
I don't.
I-I don't dislike you.

16:33.993 --> 16:36.204
I'm just...

16:36.204 --> 16:37.872
a little jealous of you sometimes.

16:37.872 --> 16:39.081
That makes sense.

16:42.210 --> 16:44.253
I'm sorry your dad
did that to you.

16:44.253 --> 16:45.671
You didn't deserve that.

16:45.671 --> 16:49.050
♪

16:49.050 --> 16:50.259
Thank you.

16:50.259 --> 16:51.677
Mm-hmm.

16:51.677 --> 16:57.058
♪

16:57.058 --> 16:58.726
You're freaking me out.
Go away.

16:58.726 --> 17:01.270
And there she is.

17:01.270 --> 17:03.856
♪

17:03.856 --> 17:06.108
Look, look.

17:06.108 --> 17:07.818
I made some man in a skirt cry.

17:07.818 --> 17:08.945
That's some
high-level widowing.

17:08.945 --> 17:10.071
I know.
[ Laughs ]

17:10.071 --> 17:11.322
[ Bagpipes groan ]

17:11.322 --> 17:13.950
Thank you.

17:13.950 --> 17:15.409
And thank you for today.

17:15.409 --> 17:16.369
My pleasure.

17:18.412 --> 17:20.581
So what happened with
your girlfriend this weekend?

17:20.581 --> 17:21.707
You never said.

17:21.707 --> 17:23.668
She was in a bad mood
after work,

17:23.668 --> 17:25.127
so I figured
I should leave her alone.

17:26.379 --> 17:28.005
Did you ask her
what was wrong?

17:29.090 --> 17:30.800
Damn it.

17:30.800 --> 17:33.553
This is why I need a magazine
list to tell me what women want.

17:33.553 --> 17:36.347
I don't know,
I think your instincts

17:36.347 --> 17:38.224
are mostly pretty good.

17:38.224 --> 17:40.935
Look, I didn't think I could
have fun without Monty

17:40.935 --> 17:43.729
at these things,
and you showed me that I can.

17:43.729 --> 17:46.899
You don't need a list
to be a catch.

17:46.899 --> 17:49.819
So...
should I delete it?

17:51.028 --> 17:52.613
Okay,
let's take a look.

17:54.323 --> 17:56.617
These are not all bad. Mm.

17:56.617 --> 17:58.286
I think your girlfriend
would want you around

17:58.286 --> 17:59.579
if you did number seven.

17:59.579 --> 18:00.788
I do number seven
all the time.

18:00.788 --> 18:02.623
She says
I'm fantastic at it.

18:02.623 --> 18:05.001
I learned a lot of stuff
from a book by Kim Cattrall.

18:05.001 --> 18:07.211
Suddenly I don't feel so bad
for your girlfriend.

18:07.211 --> 18:08.170
Look at number 10.

18:10.131 --> 18:12.383
Oh, now,
that's some crazy.

18:12.383 --> 18:13.718
Ah, hold on.

18:13.718 --> 18:20.433
♪

18:21.642 --> 18:23.769
There you are.

18:23.769 --> 18:26.230
Oh, please don't tell me
you're so drunk

18:26.230 --> 18:28.190
you think
that this is an Uber.

18:30.359 --> 18:32.028
I didn't tell Lexi off.

18:32.028 --> 18:33.654
Yeah, that's probably
for the best.

18:33.654 --> 18:34.947
I just can't believe
she said all those

18:34.947 --> 18:36.282
awful things, you know?

18:36.282 --> 18:38.034
I thought we were closer
than that.

18:38.034 --> 18:40.202
You know, when you were
in London and I had the kids,

18:40.202 --> 18:42.079
she was the only one
there for me.

18:42.079 --> 18:44.332
Oh, I suck.
I'm so sorry, Sam.

18:44.332 --> 18:45.625
No, that is
not about you.

18:45.625 --> 18:47.543
You were off living your life,
and that was great.

18:47.543 --> 18:50.921
It's just that I was here,
and I was overwhelmed,

18:50.921 --> 18:52.381
and I didn't know
what I was doing.

18:52.381 --> 18:55.092
And Lexi is the one that
helped me really figure it out,

18:55.092 --> 18:56.969
and I really
leaned on her.

18:58.554 --> 19:01.390
I think you're being hard
on Lexi.

19:01.390 --> 19:03.559
I know. Exactly, right?
It's just...

19:03.559 --> 19:04.352
Wait, what?

19:05.728 --> 19:07.980
She had some bad moments today,
for sure,

19:07.980 --> 19:10.524
but she feels really bad,

19:10.524 --> 19:13.444
and your friendship
means a lot to her.

19:13.444 --> 19:15.488
Okay, am I still drunk,
or are you saying

19:15.488 --> 19:16.697
sort of nice things
about Lexi?

19:16.697 --> 19:18.115
Girl, I'm drunk.

19:18.115 --> 19:19.784
I mean, that's the only way
to explain that.

19:19.784 --> 19:21.786
No, I'm...

19:21.786 --> 19:23.579
It's not all on her.

19:23.579 --> 19:27.833
You know, I haven't exactly been
looking for Lexi's good side.

19:27.833 --> 19:30.294
I mean, maybe it's because
she doesn't show it to me,

19:30.294 --> 19:33.005
but today
I saw a sliver of it.

19:33.005 --> 19:34.548
It was
a very small sliver,

19:34.548 --> 19:36.634
like when you go to
a super-bomb sushi restaurant,

19:36.634 --> 19:39.178
and the sushi chef cuts
that fish real thin,

19:39.178 --> 19:40.429
that it's
almost translucent.

19:40.429 --> 19:42.056
You can see the rice
through it and the wasabi--

19:42.056 --> 19:44.934
Okay. No, I get it.
I get what you're saying.

19:46.769 --> 19:49.647
I'm never gonna love Lexi,

19:49.647 --> 19:51.732
but I am so grateful
that she was there for you

19:51.732 --> 19:53.693
when I couldn't be.

19:53.693 --> 19:56.737
Anyone who cares about you
this much can't be all that bad.

19:56.737 --> 20:00.866
♪ Wake up, kids,
we got the dreamers disease ♪

20:00.866 --> 20:02.493
Nell: <i>It's funny how
the simplest lessons in life</i>

20:02.493 --> 20:04.620
<i>can seem so silly,</i>

20:04.620 --> 20:06.956
<i>but we keep coming back
to them again and again</i>

20:06.956 --> 20:08.624
<i>because they're so true.</i>

20:08.624 --> 20:09.625
Oh, thank you
very much.

20:09.625 --> 20:10.876
<i>Help each other.</i>

20:10.876 --> 20:12.753
<i>Be kind.</i>
[ Laughter ]

20:12.753 --> 20:14.547
<i>Share.</i>

20:14.547 --> 20:17.675
<i>Even if life gets more
complicated as we get older,</i>

20:17.675 --> 20:20.010
<i>if we feel left out
or left behind,</i>

20:20.010 --> 20:22.179
<i>one thing never changes.</i>

20:22.179 --> 20:25.975
Nell, we stole all the truffle
fries from Archie's Tater Shack.

20:25.975 --> 20:28.686
Get the ketchup.
Oh, and a fork.

20:28.686 --> 20:31.772
<i>Our friends are always there
for us when we need them.</i>

20:31.772 --> 20:35.025
Thanks for all the advice,
Ham Hock and Terri.

20:35.025 --> 20:37.027
Our pleasure.

20:37.027 --> 20:39.739
And always remember
to pee after sex.

20:39.739 --> 20:41.073
♪ Don't give up ♪

20:41.073 --> 20:42.450
♪ You got a reason to live ♪

20:42.450 --> 20:43.868
♪ Can't forget ♪

20:43.868 --> 20:45.286
Hey, save some for me!

20:45.286 --> 20:46.495
♪ We only get what we give ♪

20:49.123 --> 20:50.624
Ham Hock: Hi, Nell.

20:50.624 --> 20:51.834
Ham Hock?

20:51.834 --> 20:53.127
I-- What are you--

20:53.127 --> 20:55.045
Wait, how are--
I pressed send.

20:55.045 --> 20:56.422
It's me-- Tina.
Oh.

20:56.422 --> 20:57.673
I read your obit
about Terri Lawrence,

20:57.673 --> 21:00.718
and it inspired me
to pull out my old Hock Sock.

21:00.718 --> 21:04.346
Turns out, writing about crime
is so much more fun.

21:04.346 --> 21:05.973
Ham Hock:
It's usually the husband.

21:05.973 --> 21:07.475
Give me the pig.

21:07.475 --> 21:09.226
Give me the pig, Tina.

21:11.771 --> 21:18.277
♪

21:18.277 --> 21:19.403
[ As Ham Hock ]
Why are you so--

21:19.403 --> 21:20.988
[ Normal voice ] No.
[ Laughs ]

21:20.988 --> 21:23.407
Wow.
